ared baking dish and top with mashed potato. Bake for 25 - 30 minutes (180°C), or until potato is lightly browned."},{"content":"Allow to rest for 5 minutes prior to serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["See Meat stock paste recipe to make it fresh in your Thermomix. Vegetable stock paste can also be used.","Make this recipe with beef instead of lamb for a cottage pie.","Mince your own meat in the Thermomix to use in this recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","45m","6 portions"]}